{"word":"ὀρεχθέω","slug":"ὀρεχθέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n74890\" key=\"o)rexqe/w\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὀρεχθέω</orth>, <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ep.\">Ep.</a></gram> </gramGrp>Verb, once in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author></bibl>, <sense id=\"n74890.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">βόες . . ὀρέχθεον ἀμφὶ σιδήρῳ σφαζόμενοι</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:23:30\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">23.30</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>: expld. by most Gramm. of the death-<tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">rattle</tr_> in the throat (as though cogn. with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥοχθέω</foreign>) (<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κατὰ μίμησιν ἤχου τραχέος . . , ἀντὶ τοῦ ἔστενον ἀναιρούμενοι</foreign> Sch.Tad loc., cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4083.tlg001:1285:60\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eust.\">Eust.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1285.60</biblScope> </bibl> sq., <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Apollon.\">Apollon.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Lex.\">Lex.</a></title_></bibl>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author></bibl>, etc.); but also as cogn. with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀρέγομαι, ἀναιρούμενοι ὠρέγοντο ἤτοι ἐξετείνοντο</foreign> Eust.l.c. (cf. Sch. T, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Zonar.</author></bibl>, etc.), i.e. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">they were stretching themselves, struggling,</tr_> in the throes of death.—In later Poets it seems freq. to mean <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">swell up,</tr_> esp. of the heart when stirred by emotion, <xr opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"xr\"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">like</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">ὀρίνομαι, τῶς οἴεσθέ μου τὴν καρδίαν ὀρεχθεῖν</ref> </xr>; <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg003.perseus-grc1:1368\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Nu.\">Nu.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1368</biblScope> </bibl> ; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">νεάτη δ᾽ ὑπὸ κύστις ὀρεχθεῖ</foreign> the bladder <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">swells,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0022.tlg002:340\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Nic.\">Nic.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Al.\">Al.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">340</biblScope> </bibl> ; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σφακέλῳ δέ οἱ ἔνδον ὀρεχθεῖ μαινομένη κραδίη,</foreign> of a dying whale, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0023.tlg001.perseus-grc1:2:583\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Opp.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ H.\">H.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.583</biblScope> </bibl> ; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">τῇ δὲ . . δέδεται κέαρ ἔνδοθεν ἄτῃ, οὐδ᾽ ἔχει ἐκφλύξαι τόσσον γόον, ὅσσον ὀρεχθεῖ</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:275\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.R.\">A.R.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.275</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> ; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">καί οἱ ὀρέχθει θυμὸς ἐελδομένῳ στηθέων ἐξ αἷμα κεδάσσαι</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:2:49\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Id.\">Id.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.49</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>: in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0305.tlg001:6\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Aristias\">Aristias</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6</biblScope></bibl>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μύκαισι</foreign> (<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μυκαῖσι</foreign> Schneidewin) <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">δ᾽ ὠρέχθει τὸ λάϊνον πέδον,</foreign> it must have the sense of <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥοχθέω</foreign> if <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μυκαῖσι</foreign> is accepted ; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">θάλασσαν ἔα ποτὶ χερσὸν ὀρεχθεῖν</foreign> let the sea <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">roar</tr_> landwards, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0005.tlg001.perseus-grc1:11:43\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Theoc.\">Theoc.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">11.43</biblScope> </bibl> (cf. <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">βοάω</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0005.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.2</biblScope></bibl></cit>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐρεύγομαι</foreign> (B)).</sense> </entryFree>"}]}